        why_it_evolved: "There became an increased demand for paintings of scenes from history, including contemporary history, a desire for more ambitious paintings. There was a desire for propaganda institutions who could afford the art.  Execution demonstrated great technical art skill and production capability and was thus supported by the art establishments as the highest form of art. Artists reputations were built in public exhibitions rather than by impressing the owners of and visitors to palaces and public buildings. Classical history remained popular, but scenes from national histories were often the best-received. Nationalism promoted a need for a narrative of national history.",
